excerpts.text:
The words, 'Guru' and 'disciple'
Refer to but one;
The Guru alone exists as both these forms.

Even before the strings of the Vina are plucked The sound is within it;
But that sound remains unknown,
Except to itself.

There is really no action or inaction;
Everything that is happening
Is the sport of the Self.

When He is revealed, the Universe disappears;
When He is concealed, the Universe shines forth.
Yet He doesn’t hide Himself,
Nor does He reveal Himself;
He is always present before us at every moment.
